{
  "stem": "26111.5",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was presided over by a rabbi from either Germany or Austria-- I think Germany-- who was also a refugee.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And his family was there, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was the 'warden,' as they called it, of the, of the, of the hostel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auerbach.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A-U-E-R-B-A-C-H.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, he was a refugee rabbi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a refugee who was rabbi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was not a a local rabbi, no, or an English rabbi.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I lived there for-- from March '39 until [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] summer-- April, May-- of '42.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Three years, almost-- a little more than three years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As soon as I had an address, or even before, I wrote to them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I wrote them from, from Holland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wrote them from, from the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, of course, they knew that I wouldn't have a permanent address yet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They did send me some letters to the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you know, asking the kind of questions that they would.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How were things going, was I finding any, anybody-- how is this thing organized, because they had, they had very little idea how the thing was organized on the English side.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- which was doubly tough for them, because they had really no idea what they were sending me into, except it was a free country.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] That was the main thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the-- no, it was, there were family letters.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as soon as I had, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as soon as I was in Bradford and had a more or less permanent address, I-- we, we had frequent correspondence.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Which I still have, I still have most of it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At least weekly, I would say.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Until the outbreak of war, which wasn't very far away, which was only six months away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "March to September.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
